project.name: ExplorViz: Frontend API
project.description: ExplorViz: Frontend API: ExplorViz's client component for visualization

util.name: util
util.description:
This method calculates a new color with a different brightness
degree as the passed color.

params.name: brightnessDegree
params.description: The new brightness degree, e.g., '1.1' results in 10 percent lighter color

ember.name: ember
ember.description: This module holds JS-files that are necessary for every Ember application.

Landscape-Adapter.name: Landscape-Adapter
Landscape-Adapter.description:
This Adapter operates as communication abstraction for all network requests,
that refer to Landscape objects. It provides functions for fetching,
updating and uploading. However, at the time of writing this documentation
only fetching is implemented by the backend.
{{#crossLink "Landscape-Reload/updateObject:method"}}{{/crossLink}} shows an
exemplary requests.

Timestamp-Adapter.name: Timestamp-Adapter
Timestamp-Adapter.description:
This Adapter operates as communication abstraction for all network requests,
that refer to Timestamp objects. It provides functions for fetching,
updating and uploading. However, at the time of writing this documentation
only fetching is implemented by the backend.
{{#crossLink "Timeshift-Reload/updateObject:method"}}{{/crossLink}} shows an
exemplary requests.

Authenticator.name: Authenticator
Authenticator.description:
This Authenticator sends a single AJAX request with data fields "username" 
and "password" to the backend. The backend checks the authentication data 
and responds with a randomized token, if authentication was successful. This 
token is now used for all future requests by the 
{{#crossLink "Authorizer"}}{{/crossLink}}, since all backend resources are 
secured by token-based authorization. 
{{#crossLink "Authenticator/authenticate:method"}}{{/crossLink}} is called by 
{{#crossLink "Login-Form/authenticate:method"}}{{/crossLink}}.

Authorizer.name: Authorizer
Authorizer.description:
Custom authoriziers that injects the token, that is given 
by the backend and acquired by the authenticator after successful 
authentication, in every future request. This token is necessary, since all 
backend-resources (except the AuthenticationEndpoint) are secured by a 
token-based authorization mechanism.

Navbar-Glyphicons.name: Navbar-Glyphicons
Navbar-Glyphicons.description:
This component renders all components (!), that are registered in 
{{#crossLink "Page-Setup-Service"}}{{/crossLink}}, as nav-glyphicons.

Navbar-Routes.name: Navbar-Routes
Navbar-Routes.description:
This component renders all routes (!), that are registered in 
{{#crossLink "Page-Setup-Service"}}{{/crossLink}}, as nav-links.

Rendering-Core-Component.name: Rendering-Core-Component
Rendering-Core-Component.description:
This component contains the core mechanics of the different (three.js-based)
renderer. All functions below are called in a determined order, hence you only
need to override them in your custom renderer.

See {{#crossLink "Landscape-Rendering"}}{{/crossLink}} or
{{#crossLink "Application-Rendering"}}{{/crossLink}} for example usage.

Call order:

1.

Time-Shift-Component.name: Time-Shift-Component
Time-Shift-Component.description:
This component contains the core mechanics of the different (three.js-based)
renderer. All functions below are called in a determined order, hence you only
need to override them in your custom renderer.

See {{#crossLink "Landscape-Rendering"}}{{/crossLink}} or
{{#crossLink "Application-Rendering"}}{{/crossLink}} for example usage.

Call order:

1.

AggregatedClazzCommunication-Model.name: AggregatedClazzCommunication-Model
AggregatedClazzCommunication-Model.description:
Ember model for an AggregatedClazzCommunication.
Uni-directional between two clazzes

BaseEntity-Model.name: BaseEntity-Model
BaseEntity-Model.description:
Ember model for a BaseEntity. Every element of ExplorViz's Meta-Model should
inherit this class, since it might change and contain some useful data at
some point.

Component-Model.name: Component-Model
Component-Model.description: Ember model for a Component, e.g. a Java package.

CumulatedClazzCommunication-Model.name: CumulatedClazzCommunication-Model
CumulatedClazzCommunication-Model.description:
Ember model for an CumulatedClazzCommunication
Bi-directional between two clazzes

Draw3DNodeEntity-Model.name: Draw3DNodeEntity-Model
Draw3DNodeEntity-Model.description:
Ember model for a Draw3DNodeEntity. This model is inherited by all elements
that compose an application in the respective visualization.

DrawEdgeEntity-Model.name: DrawEdgeEntity-Model
DrawEdgeEntity-Model.description:
Ember model for a DrawEdgeEntity. This model is mainly used for
communications.

Data-Reload-Service.name: Data-Reload-Service
Data-Reload-Service.description:
This service is used like an abstract service. It only works with an 
"authenticated session". It will start immediatly working, when the session 
is authenticated.

Landscape-Reload-Service.name: Landscape-Reload-Service
Landscape-Reload-Service.description:
This service reloads the latest-landscape every tenth second. See
{{#crossLink "Service-Start"}}{{/crossLink}} for more information.

Timeshift-Reload-Service.name: Timeshift-Reload-Service
Timeshift-Reload-Service.description:
This service fetches the timestamps every tenth second. In addition it
reloads timestamps. {{#crossLink "Service-Start"}}{{/crossLink}} for more
information.

Application.name: Application
Application.description: Ember application is the starting point for every Ember application.

Router.name: Router
Router.description: Ember router for mapping "route" and respective "template".

classitems.description:
This overridden Ember Component lifecycle hook enables calling
ExplorViz's setup code for actual rendering and custom listeners.
classitems.name: didRender

classitems.description:
This overridden Ember Component lifecycle hook enables calling
ExplorViz's custom cleanup code.
classitems.name: willDestroyElement

classitems.description:
This function is called once on the didRender event. Inherit this function
to call other important function, e.g. "initInteraction" as shown in
{{#crossLink "Landscape-Rendering/initInteraction:method"}}{{/crossLink}}.
classitems.name: initRendering

classitems.description: This method is used to update the camera with query parameters

classitems.name: populateScene

classitems.description:
This function is called when the willDestroyElement event is fired. Inherit this
function to cleanup custom properties or unbind listener
as shown in {{#crossLink "Landscape-Rendering"}}{{/crossLink}}.
classitems.name: cleanup

classitems.description:
Inherit this function to update the scene with a new renderingModel. It
automatically removes every mesh from the scene and finally calls
the (overridden) "populateScene" function. Add your custom code
as shown in landscape-rendering.
classitems.name: cleanAndUpdateScene

classitems.description:
This function is called automatically when a new landscape was fetched. It
is executed before
{{#crossLink "Rendering-Core/cleanAndUpdateScene:method"}}{{/crossLink}}.
Inherit this function to preprocess the
{{#crossLink "Landscape"}}{{/crossLink}} for rendering, e.g. filter some
value.

See {{#crossLink "Application-Rendering"}}{{/crossLink}} for example usage.
classitems.name: preProcessEntity

classitems.description:
This attribute can be used by extensions to insert custom properties to any
meta-model object.
classitems.name: extensionAttributes

classitems.description: Indicates the line thickness (a.k.a. width) for a edge.
classitems.name: lineThickness

classitems.description:
Array for component-based settings dialogs. Any plugin may push a String 
with the name of it's settings-component in this array. See 
"color-picker-plugin" for exemplary usage.
classitems.name: pluginSettings

classitems.description: This service is used to pass data from the component to the controller.

This method is implemented in "rendering-core" to create a state out of 
the component's data, which is not contained in the model. 
This state contains the camera axis (x,y,z).

This method is used to pass the state to the controller. 
It's triggered in "rendering-core" by the function above.
This service is used to pass data from the controller to the component.

This method is implemented in the controller to create a state out of 
the controllers query parameters. 
This state contains the camera axis (x,y,z), id and timestamp.

This method is used to pass the state to the component. 
It's triggered in the controller.

The foundation is the grey all-encompassing tile. It shows 
the name of the previously clicked application and presents 
data on mouse hovering. It simply is a container for actual 
application data.
